qas.question: From which country is Bach, Mozart and Beethoven from?
In what tradition of music did Brahms Wagner and Hadyn achieve fame?
Who marked the switch from classical to romantic eras in classical music?

plausible_answers.text: Brahms, Wagner, Haydn, Schubert, Händel, Schumann

qas.question: Who are some famous Austrian composers

context: In the field of music, <a0_0>Germany<a0_0/> claims some of the most renowned classical composers of the world including <b3_0>Bach, Mozart and <a2_0>Beethoven<b3_0/><a2_0/>, who marked the transition between the Classical and Romantic eras in Western classical music. Other composers of the <a1_0>Austro-German<a1_0/> tradition who achieved international fame include <b4_0>Brahms, Wagner, Haydn, Schubert, Händel, Schumann<b4_0/>, Liszt, Mendelssohn Bartholdy, Johann Strauss II, Bruckner, Mahler, Telemann, Richard Strauss, Schoenberg, Orff, and most recently, Henze, Lachenmann, and Stockhausen.
